track_notes: 8.8 miles and 1,677 feet of gain includes short side trip to North Butte for views (none from summit).  Started bushwhack to summit from North Butte trail and almost directly north of the summit.  On way back from summit, bushwhacked northeast back to trail.  I believe there are 1 or 2 shorter options including heading north from upper parking lot, and taking alternate incline trail approaching summit from east.

Very popular hike to Oyster Dome, and the Samish Overlook parking can be very busy.  I hiked east side of loop to North Butte, and then approached summit from the north (short off-trail, but easy and found bike trail).  Descended summit to south via bike trail (unsanctioned trail),and rejoined trail just south of Lily Lake.  Then went to Oyster Dome and highly recommend this side trip for views! Total track from AllTrails tracking app was 7.4 miles and 1,421 feet gain.
track_title: Samish Overlook loop trail to Lily Lake, North Butte, Summit, and Oyster Dome
